# Paths ignored by every consumer repo, regardless of their own settings.
# Keep this list short — repo-specific exclusions belong in the consumer's
# own .semgrepignore.

# Test code: deliberately exercises bad patterns; FP rate is too high to
# be useful as a security signal.
**/tests/
**/test/
**/__tests__/
**/*_test.py
**/test_*.py

# Generated / vendored code: not under our control, scanning produces
# noise without actionable findings.
**/generated/
**/__generated__/
**/vendor/
**/node_modules/
**/.terraform/

# Build artefacts.
**/dist/
**/build/
**/__pycache__/
